Other points of interest

"Born from fire, and twice rebuilt from ashes, Downtown Toccoa's Albemarle Hotel has witnessed Toccoa's growth, and its struggles, for more than 100 years." The current structure, dating from the 1930s, incorporates elements of the original building. &#91;34&#93; For many years, it was known as the Alexander Apartments. The hotel is situated within the Downtown Toccoa Historic District and is listed on the National Register of Historic Places. &#91;35&#93;
