Kelly Barnes Dam failure

Main article: [Kelly Barnes Dam](/Kelly_Barnes_Dam)

On November 6, 1977, the earthen [Kelly Barnes Dam](/Kelly_Barnes_Dam) catastrophically failed, unleashing over 170 million gallons of water onto the campus of [Toccoa Falls College](/Toccoa_Falls_College). The disaster resulted in the tragic loss of 20 children and 19 adults. &#91;50&#93; [First Lady](/First_Lady_of_the_United_States) [Rosalynn Carter](/Rosalynn_Carter) visited Toccoa the following day to offer support. &#91;51&#93;

